[{"id":"VH966122","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a pair of horizontal, charged parallel plates that have a length of L. The bottom plate is positively charged and the top plate is negatively charged. An electron with a charge of lowercase, e, is shown moving horizontally to the right across a straight line path between the parallel plates. At a point approximately one third of the way across the parallel plates, the electron begins to curve slightly downward and to the right, exiting at the righthand end of the plates at a distance of, delta y, beneath the straight line path that it was traveling.\" height=\"232\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH966122.g01.png\" width=\"450\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An electron of charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase e\"><math alttext=\"lowercase e\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is moving to the right with velocity <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v sub 0\"><math alttext=\"v sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> when it enters the region between a pair of charged parallel plates, as shown in the figure. Assume that gravitational and edge effects are negligible and that the field between the plates is uniform and has magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase E\"><math alttext=\"uppercase E\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. After traveling the length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of the plates, the electron is displaced downward a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta y\"><math alttext=\"delta y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> from a straight-line path. Which of the following correctly describes the change, if any, in the total energy of the electron-plates system?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH966122_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It has decreased by <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase e uppercase E delta y\"><math alttext=\"lowercase e uppercase E delta y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It has increased by <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase e uppercase E delta y\"><math alttext=\"lowercase e uppercase E delta y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It has increased by <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase e uppercase E L\"><math alttext=\"lowercase e uppercase E L\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is no change.</p>"],"answer":3}]